<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>arborescens</i> and/or <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>grande</i> are dominant, co-dominant, or characteristically 
present in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Coreopsis</i> <i>gigantea</i>, <i>Diplacus</i> <i>parviflorus</i>, <i>Eriophyllum</i> <i>confertiflorum</i>, <i>Hazardia</i> <i>detonsa</i>, <i>Isocoma</i> <i>menziesii</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>dendroideus</i> and/or <i>Lupinus</i> <i>albifrons</i>. Herbs are variable in composition and cover including <i>Avena</i> spp., <i>Bromus</i> <i>diandrus</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>hordeaceus</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>madritensis</i>, <i>Selaginella</i> <i>bigelovii</i> and <i>Silene</i> <i>gallica</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrub layer is open to intermittent.  Herb layer is sparse to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Eriogonum arborescens, E. grande, </i>or <i>Hazardia detonsa</i> > 30% relative cover in the shrub canopy, yet if <i>Artemisia californica </i>or <i>Encelia californica</i> is co-dominant, see their respective alliances (Rodriguez et al. 2017).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Coastal bluffs and terraces, rocky slopes and canyon walls, stabilized dunes of coastal bars, spits along coastlines.  </div>
</div>

        
